(110, 1, '2018-05-11 19:57:58', '2018-05-11 19:57:58', 'The city of Niš has been positioned as quite a promising IT destination a couple of years ago. With over 130 IT companies and over 70 hi tech companies in Nis, it is clear that IT and hi tech are strategic priorities for this city. A few companies are even among the top 10 companies worldwide, which contributes to increasing the visibility of Nis and its IT companies on the IT map of the world. Additionally, innovation centers and hubs were established in Nis, with ELEF Annex and Techno Parks under construction.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-106\" src=\"http://badinsoft.milosevicm.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Picture3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"799\" height=\"429\" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-105 alignright\" src=\"http://badinsoft.milosevicm.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Picture2-300x158.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"158\" />Thanks to the engineering culture and genes, Nis is also a cradle of world-renowned start-up companies. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Like other major IT centers in Serbia, Niš has its own, NICAT cluster that has been recognized as a key innovation partner with a cohesive role in connecting IT companies with potential clients in the region.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.fdiintelligence.com/content/download/70984/2026095/file/fDi%20European%20Cities%20and%20Regions%20of%20the%20Future%202018:19.pdf\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Financial Times</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> has ranked Nis as the “7th city on the top 10 list of small European cities of the future for 2018/2019 when it comes to direct foreign investments”. According to this article, “Nis placed 3rd as a region on the list of top 10 small European regions for 2018/19”.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-104\" src=\"http://badinsoft.milosevicm.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Picture1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1294\" height=\"712